                     in the nonadaptive case. If even one DCP is not equal to zero, the adaptive model is a better description of firm behavior.


                  2.

The static price and advertising levels are nested within the nonadaptive price and advertising levels, that is, when
                        \documentclass{aastex} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{bm} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{pifont} \usepackage{stmaryrd} \usepackage{textcomp} \usepackage{portland,xspace} \usepackage{amsmath,amsxtra} \usepackage[OT2,OT1]{fontenc} \newcommand\cyr{ \renewcommand\rmdefault{wncyr} \renewcommand\sfdefault{wncyss} \renewcommand\encodingdefault{OT2} \normalfont \selectfont} \DeclareTextFontCommand{\textcyr}{\cyr} \pagestyle{empty} \DeclareMathSizes{10}{9}{7}{6} \begin{document} \landscape $\sigma =0$ \end{document}
                     in the nonadaptive case. This too can be tested econometrically.

The above system of equations consists of
